00:19:21,580 --> 00:19:22,140
Madam,

331
00:19:22,860 --> 00:19:24,020
it's the portraiture,
according to the priest.

332
00:20:15,020 --> 00:20:17,060
[Herbal Tea]

333
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:23,780
[Hokong Courts of Final Appeal
and Second Instance Building]

334
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:25,020
Congratulations, Mr. Lo.

335
00:20:25,060 --> 00:20:26,020
You deserve it.

336
00:20:26,140 --> 00:20:28,060
We know it's going to be you.

337
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:30,260
Thank you, everyone.

338
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:31,260
Cheers.

339
00:20:32,220 --> 00:20:33,380
I still need your support

340
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,260
in the future.

341
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:36,260
- Let's have a toast to Mr. Lo.
- Let's have a toast to Mr. Lo.

342
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,980
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

343
00:20:37,980 --> 00:20:38,820
Congratulations!

344
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:23,780
Ms. Tong,

345
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,060
I would like to file a report
about someone

346
00:21:26,380 --> 00:21:27,460
abusing their power,

347
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:29,100
stalking me and invading my privacy.

348
00:21:32,740 --> 00:21:33,940
Perhaps there's some misunderstanding.

349
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:36,940
My colleague wanted to invite you
to the station

350
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:38,580
to give us some clarification.

351
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:40,620
Maybe you just took the same route.

352
00:21:41,460 --> 00:21:42,300
I'm here now.

353
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:43,140
What do you want to ask?

354
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:51,340
What is this?

355
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:52,900
This is

356
00:21:52,940 --> 00:21:54,700
a portrait of the murderer
who killed Hon Gong.

357
00:21:55,620 --> 00:21:57,540
Mr. Chun, any thought?

358
00:22:00,460 --> 00:22:01,780
It looks familiar,

359
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:03,820
but I can't recall where I saw it.

360
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:05,700
Don't you think these eyes

361
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:07,540
look similar to yours?

362
00:22:11,980 --> 00:22:13,100
They look similar

363
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:14,580
to yours, I think.

364
00:22:20,860 --> 00:22:22,540
The time of Hon Gong's death

365
00:22:22,540 --> 00:22:24,180
was between one and two
in the afternoon.

366
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:25,140
Mr. Chun,

367
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:26,980
where were you at that time?

368
00:22:27,860 --> 00:22:29,580
Is it an official investigation?

369
00:22:30,060 --> 00:22:31,180
Shall we go to the investigation room?

370
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:32,620
Tell me where you were.

371
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:35,420
Isn't it the easiest way

372
00:22:35,580 --> 00:22:37,060
to clear your suspicion?

373
00:22:37,980 --> 00:22:39,260
We don't need to make it complicated.

374
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:41,180
For a criminal trial,

375
00:22:41,540 --> 00:22:43,540
the burden of proof
lies with the prosecution,

376
00:22:44,060 --> 00:22:46,260
and it must meet the standard
of beyond a reasonable doubt.

377
00:22:46,580 --> 00:22:47,180
The defendant

378
00:22:47,380 --> 00:22:49,180
is under no obligation
to prove his own innocence.

379
00:22:49,620 --> 00:22:51,260
Are you now refusing to answer?

380
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:53,860
Assisting the police
in their investigation

381
00:22:53,860 --> 00:22:55,380
is the duty of every citizen,

382
00:22:56,020 --> 00:22:57,460
but if certain procedures
were to be omitted

383
00:22:57,780 --> 00:22:59,500
merely because of our acquaintance,

384
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:02,460
that would be inappropriate.

385
00:23:10,380 --> 00:23:14,580
[Coffee Alley]

386
00:23:15,980 --> 00:23:16,740
Mr. Fei?

387
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:18,500
Are you Mr. Fei?

388
00:23:18,540 --> 00:23:19,060
Yes.

389
00:23:19,820 --> 00:23:20,740
I'm sorry.

390
00:23:20,780 --> 00:23:22,220
The cafe is closed.

391
00:23:22,260 --> 00:23:23,220
You can come by tomorrow.

392
00:23:24,540 --> 00:23:25,700
I'm Tong Huen, a Senior Inspector

393
00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:27,220
from Eastern District Police Station.

394
00:23:28,140 --> 00:23:29,740
What can I do for you?

395
00:23:29,980 --> 00:23:30,860
May I ask

396
00:23:30,860 --> 00:23:32,380
if you can recognize

397
00:23:32,540 --> 00:23:34,060
most of your customers?

398
00:23:35,060 --> 00:23:36,900
Most of them are regulars,

399
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:39,180
and I recognize most of them.

400
00:23:40,140 --> 00:23:41,820
This is near the court.

401
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:43,220
Are there a lot of customers

402
00:23:43,260 --> 00:23:44,340
from there?

403
00:23:44,940 --> 00:23:45,660
Yes,

404
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:47,780
like Mr. Chun.

405
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:49,380
He comes here every day.

406
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:50,460
He orders a coffee

407
00:23:50,780 --> 00:23:51,980
after lunch in the afternoon.

408
00:23:52,220 --> 00:23:53,260
He is always on time,

409
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:54,660
1:15 every day.

410
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:55,940
After all, he is a judge.

411
00:23:56,860 --> 00:23:58,500
Do you remember
if he was on time as well

412
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:00,100
last Friday?

413
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,420
Last Friday?

414
00:24:01,460 --> 00:24:02,260
Yes.

415
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:03,820
I remember that last Friday,

416
00:24:03,820 --> 00:24:04,980
there were a lot of customers.

417
00:24:05,020 --> 00:24:06,660
I almost couldn't cope.

418
00:24:06,700 --> 00:24:07,380
Then,

419
00:24:07,380 --> 00:24:08,660
when I was about to close,

420
00:24:08,700 --> 00:24:10,260
he came here and told me

421
00:24:10,540 --> 00:24:11,820
that he had lost his ring here.

422
00:24:12,340 --> 00:24:13,220
We found it

423
00:24:13,260 --> 00:24:14,900
in the sugar jar.

424
00:24:15,060 --> 00:24:15,940
That's why

425
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:17,420
I remember it very well.

426
00:24:20,780 --> 00:24:22,180
I also know Mr. Chun,

427
00:24:22,220 --> 00:24:24,100
but I don't remember

428
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:25,060
seeing him wearing a ring.

429
00:24:25,060 --> 00:24:25,740
He does.

430
00:24:26,380 --> 00:24:27,340
One time,

431
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:29,460
he accidentally spilled the coffee

432
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:30,500
and hurt himself.

433
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,060
I cleaned it for him,

434
00:24:32,060 --> 00:24:33,780
including the ring he took off.

435
00:24:37,060 --> 00:24:37,700
Madam,

436
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,300
what is this about?

437
00:24:41,380 --> 00:24:41,980
It's okay.

438
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:43,220
Thank you for your help.

439
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:44,860
Thank you.

440
00:24:44,860 --> 00:24:45,700
See you next time.

441
00:24:46,460 --> 00:24:47,420
Bye.

442
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:50,380
Alright.

443
00:24:50,580 --> 00:24:52,220
Mr. Chun has an alibi now.

444
00:24:53,060 --> 00:24:54,380
I also asked his secretary.

445
00:24:54,940 --> 00:24:55,660
She also said

446
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:57,460
that Mr. Chun had some coffee back.

447
00:24:57,940 --> 00:24:58,580
Later,

448
00:24:58,580 --> 00:25:00,340
he spilled it on a document
and asked her to print it again.

449
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:02,980
What's your thought, Madam?

450
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:07,420
Everything checks out too perfectly

451
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:09,290
to be real.

452
00:25:11,740 --> 00:25:12,620
Let's talk about it later.

453
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:19,500
[Hokong Prison]

454
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:23,740
Dad,

455
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:26,700
did you get back

456
00:25:28,060 --> 00:25:29,620
what they owe us?

457
00:25:35,460 --> 00:25:36,740
Leave these to me.

458
00:25:37,380 --> 00:25:38,380
Don't worry.

459
00:25:40,100 --> 00:25:40,860
Take care of yourself

460
00:25:40,860 --> 00:25:42,260
in there,

461
00:25:43,380 --> 00:25:44,060
alright?

462
00:26:06,820 --> 00:26:11,020
[Hokong Prison]

463
00:27:01,780 --> 00:27:02,380
Priest,

464
00:27:03,020 --> 00:27:04,820
didn't you do a portrait for the police?

465
00:27:05,740 --> 00:27:06,860
Do one for us, too.

466
00:27:07,420 --> 00:27:08,420
Life for a life.

467
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:10,780
I'm sure God

468
00:27:11,540 --> 00:27:12,460
will agree.

469
00:27:57,700 --> 00:28:00,860
[Hokong Courts of Final Appeal
and Second Instance Building]

470
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:02,260
Someone smashed Mr. Chun's car.

471
00:28:02,940 --> 00:28:04,100
I wonder who did it. Here he is.

472
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:08,580
Mr. Chun.

473
00:28:08,700 --> 00:28:09,980
- Mr. Chun.
- Mr. Chun.

474
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:11,460
Your car was vandalized last night.

475
00:28:11,460 --> 00:28:12,980
Do you know who did it?

476
00:28:13,300 --> 00:28:13,980
Mr. Chun,

477
00:28:13,980 --> 00:28:15,180
do you think it is a signal

478
00:28:15,180 --> 00:28:16,340
that security is getting worse
in Hokong?

479
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:19,500
It's nothing new

480
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:21,100
that Hokong's security is getting worse.

481
00:28:21,540 --> 00:28:22,740
If the police overlook the problem

482
00:28:23,020 --> 00:28:23,540
that the rule of law

483
00:28:23,820 --> 00:28:25,340
is being threatened by violence,

484
00:28:25,700 --> 00:28:27,740
similar incidents will happen again,

485
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:28,660
and

486
00:28:29,260 --> 00:28:30,620
it will get worse.

487
00:28:31,500 --> 00:28:32,540
I'm not afraid of the criminal,

488
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,860
and I'm willing to sacrifice anytime

489
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:36,660
for the rule of law.

490
00:28:39,940 --> 00:28:40,620
Mr. Chun,

491
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:42,780
[Self-Discipline and Impartiality]
there is a council member

492
00:28:42,780 --> 00:28:43,820
called Ong Siu who wants to meet you.

493
00:28:49,740 --> 00:28:50,540
Bring him in.

494
00:28:52,580 --> 00:28:53,860
Mr. Ong, please come in.

495
00:28:55,180 --> 00:28:56,100
Hello, Mr. Ong.

496
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:57,380
Hello, Mr. Chun.

497
00:28:57,780 --> 00:28:58,940
Because of what happened last night,

498
00:28:59,100 --> 00:29:00,180
I'm here in particular
to see how you are doing.

499
00:29:00,660 --> 00:29:01,140
Thank you.

500
00:29:01,260 --> 00:29:01,860
Take a seat.

501
00:29:02,180 --> 00:29:02,580
Sure.

502
00:29:07,380 --> 00:29:08,460
As a council member,

503
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:10,580
Other than the public,

504
00:29:10,940 --> 00:29:12,020
I also care a lot

505
00:29:12,020 --> 00:29:13,380
about the core values of Hokong.

506
00:29:14,140 --> 00:29:15,580
Economic development and the rule of law

507
00:29:15,580 --> 00:29:16,820
are closely connected.

508
00:29:16,940 --> 00:29:18,340
If the rule of law is trampled,

509
00:29:18,740 --> 00:29:21,140
I'm afraid that investors
will lose confidence in us.

510
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:23,860
Therefore, I have zero tolerance

511
00:29:24,300 --> 00:29:25,300
in terms of violence against you.

512
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:28,300
Ever since my son was sentenced to jail,

513
00:29:28,740 --> 00:29:30,780
I have suffered
from a lot of verbal violence.

514
00:29:31,380 --> 00:29:31,980
Lately,

515
00:29:31,980 --> 00:29:33,660
it has escalated to real damage.

516
00:29:34,820 --> 00:29:35,940
Yet, my biggest concern

517
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:38,340
is the safety of my son in prison.

518
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:40,460
I definitely understand your concern.

519
00:29:41,260 --> 00:29:41,820
Mr. Chun,

520
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:43,380
in fact, I'm a member
of the oversight committee

521
00:29:43,380 --> 00:29:44,700
of the Correctional Services Department

522
00:29:45,380 --> 00:29:46,900
Maybe I can directly tell the warden

523
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:48,060
to pay attention

524
00:29:48,100 --> 00:29:49,500
to your son's safety in particular?

525
00:29:50,860 --> 00:29:51,820
Is that okay?

526
00:29:52,020 --> 00:29:52,580
No problem.

527
00:29:56,180 --> 00:29:56,700
Alright.

528
00:29:58,580 --> 00:29:59,460
Hello, warden.

529
00:29:59,620 --> 00:30:00,740
I'm Mr. Ong Siu.

530
00:30:01,580 --> 00:30:02,460
Hi, Mr. Ong.

531
00:30:02,580 --> 00:30:04,180
Mr. Chun's car was vandalized

532
00:30:04,180 --> 00:30:05,220
last night.

533
00:30:05,620 --> 00:30:07,180
I'm sure you read the news, too.

534
00:30:07,340 --> 00:30:08,260
I do.

535
00:30:08,500 --> 00:30:09,940
I think this is definitely

536
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:11,580
a targeted violent behavior.

537
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:14,260
I'm worried that Chun Yat-wai,
Mr. Chun's son,

538
00:30:14,500 --> 00:30:16,380
will be the next target.

539
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:18,540
Could you please take measures

540
00:30:18,580 --> 00:30:20,140
to guarantee the safety of his son?

541
00:30:21,180 --> 00:30:22,140
Don't worry, Mr. Ong.

542
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:23,580
I know what to do.

543
00:30:23,580 --> 00:30:24,820
I will make sure Chun Yat-wai

544
00:30:24,820 --> 00:30:26,100
won't get even a scratch.

545
00:30:28,580 --> 00:30:29,500
Thank you, warden.

546
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:31,500
Stay in touch. Goodbye.

547
00:30:34,020 --> 00:30:34,500
Mr. Chun.

548
00:30:34,820 --> 00:30:36,300
The warden gives his word.

549
00:30:36,580 --> 00:30:37,820
You can rest assured.

550
00:30:38,100 --> 00:30:38,900
Thank you very much, Mr. Ong.

551
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:40,140
It's okay.

552
00:30:40,620 --> 00:30:42,180
If there's any problem in the future,

553
00:30:42,180 --> 00:30:43,380
you can contact me anytime.

554
00:30:43,740 --> 00:30:45,060
I can see that we have many chances

555
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:46,420
to work together in the future.

556
00:30:48,060 --> 00:30:49,060
Alright. I should leave.

557
00:30:49,340 --> 00:30:50,340
Alright. This way.

558
00:30:50,340 --> 00:30:50,820
Okay.

559
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:56,580
Goodbye.

560
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:57,300
Goodbye.

561
00:31:20,020 --> 00:31:20,900
Mr. Chun,

562
00:31:22,060 --> 00:31:23,180
is there a problem with your car?

563
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:25,380
Yes.

564
00:31:25,380 --> 00:31:26,700
The tire is flat.

565
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:29,220
It's difficult
to get a taxi at this hour.

566
00:31:29,540 --> 00:31:30,740
If you don't mind,

567
00:31:30,740 --> 00:31:31,500
you can take my car.

568
00:31:35,100 --> 00:31:36,140
Thank you.

569
00:31:43,740 --> 00:31:44,740
What's your name?

570
00:31:46,260 --> 00:31:47,300
Which department are you from?

571
00:31:59,100 --> 00:32:00,180
[Aspirations unmet, Rest in Heaven]
I got you here today

572
00:32:01,380 --> 00:32:02,860
as a sacrifice to my brother's death.

573
00:32:08,740 --> 00:32:09,900
Do you know that the maximum sentence

574
00:32:10,420 --> 00:32:11,940
for kidnapping is 15 years?

575
00:32:13,180 --> 00:32:14,540
You are such a good son.

576
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:16,460
Do you want to
be in prison with your father?

577
00:32:18,540 --> 00:32:19,980
15 years for kidnapping,

578
00:32:21,100 --> 00:32:22,100
then how about murder?

579
00:32:23,540 --> 00:32:24,900
What do you say you killed my brother?

580
00:32:26,060 --> 00:32:27,140
What do you want?

581
00:32:28,020 --> 00:32:29,340
Why did you kill my brother?

582
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:31,780
Do you really want an answer?

583
